President Trump addressed the American Trucking Associations in Pennsylvania, discussing his vision for America's economic revival. He emphasized his administration's commitment to tax reform, with the goal of lower taxes, bigger paychecks, and more jobs for American truckers and workers. Trump highlighted the need for a fair and simple tax system, and outlined the proposed tax cuts for everyday Americans, small businesses, and corporations. He also mentioned plans to eliminate the estate tax and incentivize American companies to bring back wealth from overseas. Trump emphasized the importance of American truckers and their role in the country's economic growth.